</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C348651FFFFD775B4AAEF919363AF8C3" pageId="5" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BED3694FFFD775B4AAEF919363AF8C3" blockId="5.[151,1437,1211,1778]" pageId="5" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis id="B926EA86FFFD775B4AAEF919345AF8FC" bold="true" box="[199,315,1716,1742]" pageId="5" pageNumber="70">Remarks.</emphasis>
Distinct from all other 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D17FFFD775B4855F91937BAF8FC" authorityName="Solier" authorityYear="1833" box="[572,731,1716,1742]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pheropsophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926EA86FFFD775B4855F91937BAF8FC" box="[572,731,1716,1742]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="70">Pheropsophus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in having four yellow wavy spots on elytra (but without humeral spot). Pronotum peculiar with strong cordiform shape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
